HEADWORD: Colatitude
<hw>Co*lat"i*tude</hw> <pr>(?; 134)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Formed
like <ets>cosine</ets>. See <er>Cosine</er>.]</ety> <def>The complement
of the latitude, or the difference between any latitude and ninety
degrees.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

